#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.1:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Sambodhivagga → sambodhavaggo (s1-3) | sambodhavagga (pts1)
msgctxt "an9.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Sambodhivagga"
msgstr "1. Awakening"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1. Sambodhisutta → sambodhipakkhiyasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Sambodhisutta"
msgstr "1. Awakening"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.351"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an9.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an9.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an9.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:2.1"
msgid "“Sace, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow other paths were to ask:"

#. VAR: sambodhipakkhikānaṃ → sambodhipakkhiyānaṃ (bj) | sambodhapakkhikānaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.1:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘sambodhipakkhikānaṃ, āvuso, dhammānaṃ kā upanisā bhāvanāyā’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā "
"tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ kinti "
"byākareyyāthā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, what is the vital condition for the development of the awakening "
"factors?’ How would you answer them?”"

msgctxt "an9.1:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū "
"dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” The mendicants will listen and "
"remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:3.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an9.1:3.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an9.1:3.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:4.1"
msgid "“Sace, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow other paths were to ask:"

msgctxt "an9.1:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘sambodhipakkhikānaṃ, āvuso, dhammānaṃ kā upanisā bhāvanāyā’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā "
"tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, what is the vital condition for the development of the awakening "
"factors?’ You should answer them:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.352"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:5.1"
msgid "‘Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko."
msgstr "‘It’s when a mendicant has good friends, companions, and associates."

msgctxt "an9.1:5.2"
msgid ""
"Sambodhipakkhikānaṃ, āvuso, dhammānaṃ ayaṃ paṭhamā upanisā bhāvanāya. (1)"
msgstr ""
"This is the first vital condition for the development of the awakening "
"factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu. (2)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and "
"has appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an9.1:6.2"
msgid "Sambodhipakkhikānaṃ, āvuso, dhammānaṃ ayaṃ dutiyā upanisā bhāvanāya."
msgstr ""
"This is the second vital condition for the development of the awakening "
"factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu yāyaṃ kathā abhisallekhikā cetovivaraṇasappāyā, "
"seyyathidaṃ—appicchakathā santuṭṭhikathā pavivekakathā asaṃsaggakathā "
"vīriyārambhakathā sīlakathā samādhikathā paññākathā vimuttikathā "
"vimuttiñāṇadassanakathā, evarūpiyā kathāya nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī "
"akasiralābhī."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant gets to take part in talk about self-effacement "
"that helps open the heart, when they want, without trouble or difficulty. "
"That is, talk about fewness of wishes, contentment, seclusion, keeping your "
"distance, arousing energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the "
"knowledge and vision of freedom."

msgctxt "an9.1:7.2"
msgid ""
"Sambodhipakkhikānaṃ, āvuso, dhammānaṃ ayaṃ tatiyā upanisā bhāvanāya. (3)"
msgstr ""
"This is the third vital condition for the development of the awakening "
"factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo "
"anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up "
"unskillful qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They are strong, "
"staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful "
"qualities."

msgctxt "an9.1:8.2"
msgid ""
"Sambodhipakkhikānaṃ, āvuso, dhammānaṃ ayaṃ catutthī upanisā bhāvanāya. (4)"
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth vital condition for the development of the awakening "
"factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:9.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

# Note that both text and BB mark the end of the initial answer here, but there is no “ti” to support this in the text. The sutta is obviously a composite one.
msgctxt "an9.1:9.2"
msgid "Sambodhipakkhikānaṃ, āvuso, dhammānaṃ ayaṃ pañcamī upanisā bhāvanāya’."
msgstr ""
"This is the fifth vital condition for the development of the awakening "
"factors.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:10.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa—"
msgstr "A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to"

msgctxt "an9.1:10.2"
msgid ""
"sīlavā bhavissati, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharissati ācāragocarasampanno "
"aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhissati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr "be ethical …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:11.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa—"
msgstr "A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to"

msgctxt "an9.1:11.2"
msgid ""
"yāyaṃ kathā abhisallekhikā cetovivaraṇasappāyā, seyyathidaṃ—appicchakathā "
"santuṭṭhikathā pavivekakathā asaṃsaggakathā vīriyārambhakathā sīlakathā "
"samādhikathā paññākathā vimuttikathā vimuttiñāṇadassanakathā, evarūpiyā "
"kathāya nikāmalābhī bhavissati akicchalābhī akasiralābhī."
msgstr "take part in talk about self-effacement that helps open the heart …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.353"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:12.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa—"
msgstr "A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to"

msgctxt "an9.1:12.2"
msgid ""
"āraddhavīriyo viharissati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr "live with energy roused up …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an9.1:13.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa—"
msgstr "A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to"

msgctxt "an9.1:13.2"
msgid ""
"paññavā bhavissati udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya "
"nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā. (5)"
msgstr "be wise …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.1:14.1"
msgid ""
"Tena ca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā imesu pañcasu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya cattāro "
"dhammā uttari bhāvetabbā—"
msgstr ""
"A mendicant grounded on these five things should develop four further things."

#. VAR: ānāpānassati → ānāpānasati (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.1:14.2"
msgid ""
"asubhā bhāvetabbā rāgassa pahānāya, mettā bhāvetabbā byāpādassa pahānāya, "
"ānāpānassati bhāvetabbā vitakkupacchedāya, aniccasaññā bhāvetabbā "
"asmimānasamugghātāya."
msgstr ""
"They should develop the perception of ugliness to give up greed, love to "
"give up hate, mindfulness of breathing to cut off thinking, and perception "
"of impermanence to uproot the conceit ‘I am’."

msgctxt "an9.1:14.3"
msgid "Aniccasaññino, bhikkhave, anattasaññā saṇṭhāti."
msgstr ""
"When you perceive impermanence, the perception of not-self becomes "
"stabilized."

msgctxt "an9.1:14.4"
msgid ""
"Anattasaññī asmimānasamugghātaṃ pāpuṇāti diṭṭheva dhamme nibbānan”ti. (6–9.)"
msgstr ""
"Perceiving not-self, you uproot the conceit ‘I am’ and attain extinguishment "
"in this very life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.1:14.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
